"{\"uid\": \"straitstimes.com-sport-paris-lean-olympics-won-t-blow-any-budgets-credit-rating-firm-sp-says\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Choose edition  Search  singapore  asia  world  opinion  life  business  sport  Visual  Podcasts  SPH Rewards  STClassifieds  Paid press releases  Advertise with us  FAQs  Contact us  Sign up now:Get the biggest sports news in your inbox  The near \\u20ac9 billion (S$13.1 billion) budget to host the July 26-Aug 11 Games is comfortably below those of Tokyo, Rio and London.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 98, \"end\": 101, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.001452184829566e-14, \"text\": \"SPH\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Singapore_Press_Holdings\"}, {\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"score\": 0.9604822703099307, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Advertise\", \"types\": [\"Q7377\", \"Q729\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Advertise_(horse)\"}, {\"begin\": 346, \"end\": 351, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.6003516318257614e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9212184964934567, \"rank\": 0.0854841431959943, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 361, \"end\": 367, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999914878056498, \"rank\": 6.1020526273447574e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"PHOTO: REUTERS  PublishedMar 12, 2024, 02:03 PM  UpdatedMar 12, 2024, 11:42 PM  LONDON-Paris' \\\"lean\\\" Olympics are unlikely to do any lasting damage to France's finances, thanks to 95 per cent of its venues either already being built or needing only minor refurbishment, credit rating agency S&P Global estimated in a report on March 11.\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 706, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 377, \"end\": 384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"REUTERS\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}, {\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997159157426937, \"rank\": 0.00021131481214296956, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The near \\u20ac9 billion (S$13.1 billion) budget to hostthe July 26-Aug 11 Gamesis comfortably below those of Tokyo, Rio and London, and only a fraction of the record US$52.7 billion (S$70.3 billion) Beijing is estimated to have spent in 2008.\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 946, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 813, \"end\": 818, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.6003516318257614e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 823, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9212184964934567, \"rank\": 0.0854841431959943, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}, {\"begin\": 828, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999914878056498, \"rank\": 6.1020526273447574e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' main outlays have included just three major builds - its Olympics Village expected to cost about \\u20ac1.5 billion, the Aquatics Centre at \\u20ac175 million and a \\u20ac138 million badminton and gymnastics arena.\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 1151, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 947, \"end\": 952, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999272404, \"rank\": 7.261515500995143e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We do not expect the Games to weigh significantly on French public-sector entities, including Paris and the central government,\\\" said S&P, which specialises in assessing creditworthiness.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1207, \"end\": 1213, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.67359425087961, \"rank\": 0.4816048039209548, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1248, \"end\": 1253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999272404, \"rank\": 7.261515500995143e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"score\": 0.9619105199517101, \"rank\": 0.02776031845799459, \"text\": \"S&P\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The budget is expected to be evenly split between \\u20ac4.5 billion being spent on new venues and facilities and the other \\u20ac4.4 billion on related operating expenses such as hosting and running transport networks.\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, S&P's AA credit rating on France is two steps below the AAA maximum countries can have.\", \"from\": 1553, \"to\": 1649, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1562, \"end\": 1565, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"score\": 0.9619105199517101, \"rank\": 0.02776031845799459, \"text\": \"S&P\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\"}, {\"begin\": 1588, \"end\": 1594, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997159157426937, \"rank\": 0.00021131481214296956, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1618, \"end\": 1621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999426171396418, \"rank\": 5.637263804160317e-05, \"text\": \"AAA\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_Automobile_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also has a \\\"negative outlook\\\" on the country, which is a red flag that the rating could get cut.\", \"from\": 1650, \"to\": 1749, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's overall public spending on the Games, including by the state and local and regional authorities like Paris, will be only 28 per cent of the total budget S&P estimates.\", \"from\": 1751, \"to\": 1927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997159157426937, \"rank\": 0.00021131481214296956, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1861, \"end\": 1866, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999272404, \"rank\": 7.261515500995143e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1916, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"score\": 0.9619105199517101, \"rank\": 0.02776031845799459, \"text\": \"S&P\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ticket sales and TV and marketing deals should bring in around \\u20ac4.2 billion which could cover up to 96 per cent of total operating costs, according to the International Olympic Committee (IOC).\", \"from\": 1929, \"to\": 2122, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2084, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France's government has agreed to provide the IOC with a \\u20ac3 billion guarantee, which equates to 0.1 per cent of its gross domestic product.\", \"from\": 2124, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2124, \"end\": 2130, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9997159157426937, \"rank\": 0.00021131481214296956, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2170, \"end\": 2173, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.76514467354644e-14, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tax windfall from full hotels and restaurants and other visitor-related spending should also help cover the bill, with the government saying the economic benefits could be as high as \\u20ac10 billion.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Cost overruns remain a risk, however, if past Games are anything to go by.\", \"from\": 2466, \"to\": 2540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"London's 2012 Olympics overspent by more than US$5 billion.\", \"from\": 2542, \"to\": 2601, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2542, \"end\": 2548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999914878056498, \"rank\": 6.1020526273447574e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo overran by nearly US$26 billion after the Covid-19 pandemic forced it to delay its 2020 Games by eight months and then spectators were not allowed, while the state of Rio de Janeiro defaulted in 2016 after the cost of its Games saw its debt levels soar.\", \"from\": 2602, \"to\": 2861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2602, \"end\": 2607, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999999999996362, \"rank\": 3.6003516318257614e-12, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2775, \"end\": 2789, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 0.9999999999195097, \"rank\": 8.046392437772827e-11, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Montreal remains the worst example in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2917, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2863, \"end\": 2871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 0.9999095414325775, \"rank\": 5.790338628705467e-05, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The bill came in at 13 times the original estimate and the cost of the main stadium took more than 30 years to repay in full.\", \"from\": 2918, \"to\": 3043, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris' infrastructure spending has overshot the initial budget by over 37 per cent compared with its 2016 projection although it is more moderate by 14 percentage points once inflation is factored in.\", \"from\": 3045, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3045, \"end\": 3050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999272404, \"rank\": 7.261515500995143e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Its operating expense budget has ballooned 15 per cent compared with 2019 estimates.\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3331, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"With the Games yet to happen, budgetary slippages are still a risk,\\\" S&P added.REUTERS  Olympics  Olympics 2024  France  E-paper  Newsletters  Podcasts  RSS Feed  About Us  Terms & Conditions  Personal Data Protection Notice  Need help?\", \"from\": 3333, \"to\": 3570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3403, \"end\": 3406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"score\": 0.9619105199517101, \"rank\": 0.02776031845799459, \"text\": \"S&P\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/S&P_Global_Ratings\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Reach us here.\", \"from\": 3571, \"to\": 3585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Advertise with us\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": []}]}"